Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Quick service and very friendly server! All smiles and good food. Not to expensive either: good value for money. Fruit beers are good too, but very sweet.

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Very good restaurant with Ethiopian meals. It tastes very good, the meals are spicy. You have all ordered dish on one injara and you can share with your friends. And for dessert cinnamon glaces with coffee and liquor. All things really delicious!

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Authentic little Ethiopian restaurant with interesting art and decor and instrumental lounge music. The staff are very friendly. ‚Ä¶

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Great Ethiopian experience! delicious food that rewards a long waiting time for it in a very warm room. The restaurant staff were very friendly and smiley. I will definitely be back.

Name: Lalibela

Name: Lalibela

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Good options, decent food, but leaves something to be desired. The mango beer was delicious

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Perhaps my favorite Ethiopian restaurant outside of Ethiopian (and I eat Ethiopian in any city that has it!) the mixed vegetarian plate and mixed meat plate is a great place to start. Love the farmers cheese, kitfo, and greens.

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Lalibela is a nice little Ethiopian restaurant. The food is quite delicious and I like the way they serve.

Name: Lalibela

Name: Lalibela

Name: Lalibela

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Worthy of a Michelin star! Fantastic flavours and authentic Ethiopian cuisine. Really friendly service, great prices and wonderful ambience. One of the best meals I‚Äôve eaten in years.

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: An amazing dining experience.  If you've never had Ehtiopian food or were just thinking about it, I highly suggest Lalibela.  They help ease you into the spice and will take the time to thoroughly explain their dishes.  Menu is in both Dutch and English - big plus!  Thank you so much!

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Wow wow, it was my first time trying Ethiopian food and I wasn't sure what to expect, but it was delicious! I want to go back already. The mango beer was great too, served in a coconut. And the prices were good.

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Good food and decent service. Portions are a bit smaller than other Ethiopian restaurants in the city but the quality of the food makes up for it. Worth a visit.

Name: Lalibela
Review Text: Pretty fast for the type of food you‚Äôre getting, and delicious food, too! I have been twice and both times were wonderful. The vegan and vegetarian options were a hit with everyone, including the omnivores.

Name: Lalibela

Name: Lalibela
